steps.instruction:
### Prep
- Half the squash
- Finely chop the thyme

Note: If using whole squash, cut in half lengthwise, then scoop out and discard seeds before beginning recipe

### Steps
1. Cut 1/2 inch off the top and bottom of squash halves
2. Remove and discard seeds from squash halves, then place cut-side-down in 9-inch square microwave-safe dish
3. Pour water over squash; cover and microwave on HIGH for 8 minutes
4. Uncover carefully and let stand 10 minutes or until cool enough to handle
5. Preheat oven to 400F. Chop thyme (1/2 teaspoon); whisk with remaining ingredients until glaze is blended
6. Transfer squash to cutting board and peel
7. Cut most of the way through each squash (with a serrated knife) at 1/4-inch intervals (about 2030 cuts), leaving 1/4 inch intact
8. Place squash in baking dish
9. Brush glaze over top and in between cuts
10. Bake 2025 minutes or until fork-tender and glaze caramelizes
11. Brush with any remaining glaze; serve
